node.title: Man found dead in parked car on Raglan street
node.description: Waikato police are investigating after a man's body was found in a parked car in the seaside town of Raglan last night.
node.content:
["Waikato police are investigating after a man's body was found in a parked car in the seaside town of Raglan last night.", "", "
\nPhoto: RNZ / Patrice Allen\n
", "A cordon is now in place at a residential address on Wainui Road and a scene examination is under way.", "Police are appealing for any sightings of a white Mitsubishi Legnum in Raglan yesterday afternoon.", "They also want to hear from anyone who saw suspicious or disorderly behaviour.", "Detective Inspector Graham Pitkethley said the cordon was put in place overnight and will remain for some time.", "Anyone with information is asked to contact police on 105 and refer to file number 220126/6493.", "They can also call Crime Stoppers anonymously on 0800 555 111."]
